The paper proposes a learning-based model for mastering MOBA games, which involves decision-making in a partially observable environment with a large action space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The model also involves training agents to make macro strategy decisions and communicate with allies, which could fall under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Game Theory (cs.GT), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL).
